{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "06", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "22", "M": "23", "S": "44"}}, "news": [{"title": "\u20b960 Crore mega residential deal: DGS Group promoters Brahamdev Shukla, Sourav Shukla & Rohan Shukla snap up luxury unit at Oberoi Elysian, Goregaon East", "para": "Mumbai's luxury housing market sees a major deal. Brahamdev Shukla, Sourav Shukla, and Rohan Shukla of DGS Group have bought a \u20b960 crore apartment in Oberoi Elysian, Goregaon East. This large acquisition highlights Goregaon East's growing appeal to wealthy buyers. The project is currently under construction.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/brand-connect-initiative/60-crore-mega-residential-deal-dgs-group-promoters-brahamdev-shukla-sourav-shukla-rohan-shukla-snap-up-luxury-unit-at-oberoi-elysian-goregaon-east/130058875?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-73760/130058875.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "brand-connect-initiative"}, {"title": "Max Estates reports \u20b95,305 crore pre-sales in FY26", "para": "Max Estates reported pre-sales of \u20b95,305 crore in FY2026, with the March quarter contributing \u20b93,392 crore. Key projects like Estate 105 in Noida and Estate 361 in Gurugram drove these strong sales. The company's net debt stood at approximately \u20b9174 crore as of March 2026, with a robust project pipeline valued over \u20b916,000 crore.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/max-estates-achieves-5305-crore-in-pre-sales-for-fy26-driven-by-robust-march-quarter-performance/130060369?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-9834/130060369.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Ahmedabad civic body puts parking onus on property owners", "para": "Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation has implemented strict new parking regulations, placing the onus on property owners to manage vehicle parking within their premises. Non-compliance risks building usage permission suspension, with owners now responsible for preventing street parking and ensuring clear, marked bays. Buildings must also remove obstructions and submit annual self-declarations regarding parking area integrity.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/ahmedabad-civic-body-enforces-new-parking-regulations-on-property-owners/130049159?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-197336/130049159.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}